{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847457681,"sessionID":"ses_2873ec91affe5CwFjLTC3zhF4t","part":{"id":"prt_d78c1b478001d2tLhSZmPYBe4o","messageID":"msg_d78c1a3b1001qp3eoD6pl76xk5","sessionID":"ses_2873ec91affe5CwFjLTC3zhF4t","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f76f1d86902f439ca49fe190","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`ŌåÆ`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` ŌåÆ `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775847457664,"end":1775847457680}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847457683,"sessionID":"ses_2873ec91affe5CwFjLTC3zhF4t","part":{"id":"prt_d78c1b950001eGJHkOx9a6YNXL","messageID":"msg_d78c1a3b1001qp3eoD6pl76xk5","sessionID":"ses_2873ec91affe5CwFjLTC3zhF4t","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_63ad03027796419b9d5bf19f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/client-go.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/client-go.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # client-go library\n2: \n3: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n4: \n5: ## Clientset\n6: \n7: ### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: type Interface interface {\n11: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n12: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n13: }\n14: ```\n15: \n16: ### `Clientset` struct\n17: \n18: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n19: \n20: **Constructors**\n21: \n22: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n23: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n24: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n25: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n26: \n27: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Typed client ŌĆö `runtime/v1alpha1`\n32: \n33: ### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n34: \n35: ```go\n36: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n37: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n38: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n39: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n40: }\n41: ```\n42: \n43: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n44: \n45: ### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n46: \n47: ```go\n48: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n49: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n50: }\n51: \n52: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n53: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n54: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n55: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n56: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n57: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n58: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n59: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n60: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n61: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n62: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n63: }\n64: ```\n65: \n66: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n67: \n68: ### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n69: \n70: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n71: \n72: ### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: type AgentRuntimeExpansion interface{}\n76: type CodeInterpreterExpansion interface{}\n77: ```\n78: \n79: (Empty ŌĆö reserved for custom methods.)\n80: \n81: ### Fake clients (`typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/`)\n82: \n83: `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` ŌĆö test doubles implementing the typed interfaces; `doc.go` markers.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## Scheme (`clientset/versioned/scheme/`)\n88: \n89: | File | Role |\n90: |------|------|\n91: | `register.go` | Builds `Scheme`, `Codecs`, `ParameterCodec`; `AddToScheme` registers `runtime/v1alpha1` types |\n92: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## Informer factory\n97: \n98: ### `SharedInformerFactory` (`informers/externalversions/factory.go`)\n99: \n100: ```go\n101: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n102: \tinternalinterfaces.SharedInformerFactory\n103: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n104: \tShutdown()\n105: \tWaitForCacheSync(stopCh <-chan struct{}) map[reflect.Type]bool\n106: \tForResource(resource schema.GroupVersionResource) (GenericInformer, error)\n107: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n108: \tRuntime() externalversionsruntime.Interface\n109: }\n110: ```\n111: \n112: **Constructors / options**\n113: \n114: - `NewSharedInformerFactory(client versioned.Interface, defaultResync time.Duration)`\n115: - `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, defaultResync, options ...SharedInformerOption)`\n116: - `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` (deprecated alias to WithOptions)\n117: - Options: `WithCustomResyncConfig`, `WithTweakListOptions`, `WithNamespace`, `WithTransform`\n118: \n119: ### Group interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`)\n120: \n121: ```go\n122: type Interface interface {\n123: \tV1alpha1() v1alpha1.Interface\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: `New(factory, namespace, tweakListOptions)` returns group accessor.\n128: \n129: ### Version interface (`informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`)\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: type Interface interface {\n133: \tAgentRuntimes() AgentRuntimeInformer\n134: \tCodeInterpreters() CodeInterpreterInformer\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ### Per-type informers (`.../runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`, `codeinterpreter.go`)\n139: \n140: Example (`AgentRuntimeInformer`):\n141: \n142: ```go\n143: type AgentRuntimeInformer interface {\n144: \tInformer() cache.SharedIndexInformer\n145: \tLister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: Also provides `NewAgentRuntimeInformer`, `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer`, and analogous constructors for CodeInterpreter.\n150: \n151: ### Generic resource routing (`informers/externalversions/generic.go`)\n152: \n153: `ForResource` switches on:\n154: \n155: - `v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\")` ŌåÆ `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n156: - `...WithResource(\"codeinterpreters\")` ŌåÆ `...CodeInterpreters().Informer()`\n157: \n158: ### `internalinterfaces` (`informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go`)\n159: \n160: ```go\n161: type NewInformerFunc func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n162: type SharedInformerFactory interface {\n163: \tStart(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n164: \tInformerFor(obj runtime.Object, newFunc NewInformerFunc) cache.SharedIndexInformer\n165: }\n166: type TweakListOptionsFunc func(*metav1.ListOptions)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ## Listers (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`)\n172: \n173: ### `AgentRuntimeLister` / `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` (`agentruntime.go`)\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n177: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n178: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n179: \tAgentRuntimeListerExpansion\n180: }\n181: \n182: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n183: \tList(selector labels.Selector) ([]*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n184: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n185: \tAgentRuntimeNamespaceListerExpansion\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: `NewAgentRuntimeLister` uses `runtimev1alpha1.Resource(\"agentruntime\").GroupResource()`.\n190: \n191: ### `CodeInterpreterLister` / `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` (`codeinterpreter.go`)\n192: \n193: Same pattern for `CodeInterpreter`; `NewCodeInterpreterLister` uses `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()`.\n194: \n195: ### Expansion (`expansion_generated.go`)\n196: \n197: Empty expansion interfaces for listers and namespace listers (all four types).\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Fake clientset (`clientset/versioned/fake/`)\n202: \n203: | File | Role |\n204: |------|------|\n205: | `clientset_generated.go` | `NewSimpleClientset`, `NewClientset` ŌĆö in-memory fake `Clientset` |\n206: | `register.go` | Scheme registration for fakes |\n207: | `doc.go` | Package doc |\n208: \n209: ---\n210: \n211: ## File index (all paths under `client-go/`)\n212: \n213: | Path | Role |\n214: |------|------|\n215: | `clientset/versioned/clientset.go` | `Clientset`, `Interface`, constructors |\n216: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` | Scheme / codecs for generated client |\n217: | `clientset/versioned/scheme/doc.go` | Doc |\n218: | `clientset/versioned/fake/clientset_generated.go` | Fake clientset implementation |\n219: | `clientset/versioned/fake/register.go` | Fake scheme wiring |\n220: | `clientset/versioned/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n221: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go` | `RuntimeV1alpha1Client`, `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` |\n222: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeInterface`, typed REST client |\n223: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterInterface`, typed REST client |\n224: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` | Expansion interfaces |\n225: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Doc |\n226: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_runtime_client.go` | Fake runtime group client |\n227: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_agentruntime.go` | Fake AgentRuntime client |\n228: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` | Fake CodeInterpreter client |\n229: | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/doc.go` | Doc |\n230: | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | `SharedInformerFactory`, options, `Start`/`Shutdown`/`WaitForCacheSync` |\n231: | `informers/externalversions/generic.go` | `GenericInformer`, `ForResource` |\n232: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go` | Group `runtime` informer accessor |\n233: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go` | `v1alpha1` informer accessors |\n234: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime informer + constructor |\n235: | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter informer + constructor |\n236: | `informers/externalversions/internalinterfaces/factory_interfaces.go` | Small factory interface + `NewInformerFunc`, `TweakListOptionsFunc` |\n237: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | `AgentRuntimeLister`, namespace lister |\n238: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | `CodeInterpreterLister`, namespace lister |\n239: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go` | Lister expansion interfaces |\n240: \n241: **Regeneration:** `make gen-client` ŌåÆ `hack/update-codegen.sh` (`k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch`, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`).\n\n(End of file - total 241 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# client-go library\n\nGenerated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n\n## Clientset\n\n### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n\tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n\tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n### `Clientset` struct\n\nEmbeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n\n**Constructors**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/client-go.md","time":{"start":1775847457668,"end":1775847457682}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775847457687,"sessionID":"ses_2873ec91affe5CwFjLTC3zhF4t","part":{"id":"prt_d78c1be4e001NV7LW8v2F4sU86","messageID":"msg_d78c1a3b1001qp3eoD6pl76xk5","sessionID":"ses_2873ec91affe5CwFjLTC3zhF4t","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_03c89df307574e3da2b3f955","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 ŌĆö CRD CodeInterpreter ń▒╗Õ×ŗÕ«Üõ╣ē Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the CodeInterpreter CRD type implementation including Go API types, validation, CRD manifests, client-go library, informers, and listers for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter API type definition\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterSpec` types. `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL include `runtimeRef` (string), `code` (string), `language` (string), `executionPolicy` (ExecutionPolicy), and `resources` (ResourceQuota). `CodeInterpreter` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type registration\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n16: - **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&CodeInterpreter{}, &CodeInterpreterList{})` is called during init\n17: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be registered in the scheme with `Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`, `APIVersion = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\"`\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Runtime reference binding\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter YAML with `spec.runtimeRef: \"python-3.11\"`\n22: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed by the scheme\n23: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.RuntimeRef` SHALL be populated with the runtime name string\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Code field parsing\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** `spec.code` contains Python code string\n28: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is deserialized\n29: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Code` SHALL contain the exact code string\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Language specification\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** `spec.language: \"python\"` or `spec.language: \"go\"`\n34: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed\n35: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Language` SHALL be populated with the language identifier\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Execution policy configuration\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** `spec.executionPolicy` with `timeout: \"30s\"` and `maxRetries: 3`\n40: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed\n41: - **THEN** `ExecutionPolicy.Timeout` (metav1.Duration) and `ExecutionPolicy.MaxRetries` (int32) SHALL be populated\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Resource quota binding\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `spec.resources` specifies `cpu: \"500m\"`, `memory: \"512Mi\"`, `storage: \"1Gi\"`\n46: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is validated by the scheme\n47: - **THEN** `Resources` SHALL be of type `ResourceQuota` with parsed values\n48: \n49: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter status subresource\n50: \n51: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with `Phase` (CodeInterpreterPhase), `Conditions` ([]CodeInterpreterCondition), `Result` (string), `ExecutionTime` (metav1.Duration), and `LastTransitionTime` (metav1.Time). `CodeInterpreter` SHALL expose `.status` via the status subresource.\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Status phase transitions\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `status.phase = \"Pending\"`\n56: - **WHEN** the controller updates status to `\"Running\"` then to `\"Succeeded\"`\n57: - **THEN** `LastTransitionTime` SHALL be updated for each transition and Conditions appended\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Condition management\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** a condition of type `\"Ready\"` with `status: \"True\"`, `reason: \"ExecutionComplete\"`, `message: \"Code executed successfully\"`\n62: - **WHEN** status is updated via the status subresource\n63: - **THEN** the condition SHALL be upserted into `status.conditions` with `lastTransitionTime` set\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Execution result storage\n66: \n67: - **GIVEN** code execution completes with output\n68: - **WHEN** the controller sets `status.result` to the execution output\n69: - **THEN** `status.result` SHALL contain the stdout/stderr of code execution\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Execution time tracking\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** code execution takes 5.2 seconds\n74: - **WHEN** the controller updates `status.executionTime`\n75: - **THEN** `status.executionTime.Duration` SHALL be `5.2s`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter phase and condition types\n78: \n79: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterPhase` constants: `Pending`, `Running`, `Succeeded`, `Failed`, `Terminating`. The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterConditionType` constants: `Ready`, `Executing`, `Completed`.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Phase constant availability\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n84: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning` is referenced\n85: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"Running\"`\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Condition type constant availability\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n90: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterConditionReady` is referenced\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"Ready\"`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Condition structure\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterCondition` is created\n96: - **WHEN** fields are set: `Type`, `Status`, `Reason`, `Message`, `LastTransitionTime`\n97: - **THEN** the condition SHALL match the structure of `AgentRuntimeCondition`\n98: \n99: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter validation\n100: \n101: The system SHALL implement `ValidateCodeInterpreter(obj *CodeInterpreter) field.ErrorList` in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go`. Validation SHALL check: `runtimeRef` is non-empty, `code` is non-empty, `language` is valid (python, go, nodejs), `resources` are valid quantities.\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Valid CodeInterpreter validation\n104: \n105: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `runtimeRef: \"python-3.11\"`, `code: \"print('hello')\"`, `language: \"python\"`\n106: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n107: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL be empty\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Missing runtimeRef validation\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `runtimeRef`\n112: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n113: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.runtimeRef` with reason `Required`\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Missing code validation\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `code`\n118: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n119: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.code` with reason `Required`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Invalid language validation\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `language: \"invalid\"`\n124: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n125: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.language` with reason `NotSupported`\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Invalid resource quantity validation\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `resources.cpu: \"invalid\"`\n130: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n131: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.resources.cpu` with reason `Invalid`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Status update phase transition validation\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `status.phase = \"Succeeded\"`\n136: - **WHEN** controller attempts to update phase to `\"Running\"` via `ValidateCodeInterpreterStatusUpdate`\n137: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain a `Forbidden` error for invalid phase transition\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: CRD manifest generation\n140: \n141: The system SHALL generate `manifests/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` via `make gen-crd` using controller-gen.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD with status subresource\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** `+genclient` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers on `CodeInterpreter`\n146: - **WHEN** `make gen-crd` runs controller-gen\n147: - **THEN** the CRD manifest SHALL include `spec.subresources.status: {}`\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: CRD schema validation for required fields\n150: \n151: - **GIVEN** `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` markers on `runtimeRef` and `code`\n152: - **WHEN** CRDs are generated\n153: - **THEN** the OpenAPI v3 schema SHALL mark `runtimeRef` and `code` as required\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: CRD group and version\n156: \n157: - **GIVEN** `SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n158: - **WHEN** CRDs render\n159: - **THEN** `metadata.name` SHALL be `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` and `spec.group = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: CRD printer columns\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` markers on `CodeInterpreter`\n164: - **WHEN** CRDs are generated\n165: - **THEN** the CRD SHALL include printer columns for NAME, PHASE, RUNTIME, and AGE\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: client-go typed client for CodeInterpreter\n168: \n169: The system SHALL generate typed client under `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `CodeInterpreterInterface` providing `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch` methods.\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Create CodeInterpreter via typed client\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** a configured `Clientset` and valid `CodeInterpreter` object\n174: - **WHEN** `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(ctx, ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n175: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be created via the K8s API and returned with populated metadata\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Update status via typed client\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter with a mutable status\n180: - **WHEN** `UpdateStatus(ctx, ci, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` is called\n181: - **THEN** only the status subresource SHALL be updated\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: List with label selector\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters with labels `app=runner` in namespace `default`\n186: - **WHEN** `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=runner\"})` is called\n187: - **THEN** only matching CodeInterpreters SHALL be returned\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Watch for changes\n190: \n191: - **GIVEN** a watch on `CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n192: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created or updated\n193: - **THEN** the watch channel SHALL receive an `Event` with `Type` and `Object`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Delete by name\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `exec-1` exists\n198: - **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, \"exec-1\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})` is called\n199: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from the API server\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Patch update\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n204: - **WHEN** `Patch(ctx, \"exec-1\", types.MergePatchType, data, metav1.PatchOptions{})` is called\n205: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be partially updated with patch data\n206: \n207: ### Requirement: Informer factory for CodeInterpreter\n208: \n209: The system SHALL generate informer under `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `CodeInterpreterInformer` and methods `Informer()`, `Lister()`, `NewCodeInterpreterInformer`, `NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer`.\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Start informer for CodeInterpreters\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** a configured `SharedInformerFactory`\n214: - **WHEN** `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` is called and `factory.Start(stopCh)` runs\n215: - **THEN** the informer SHALL list-watch `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and populate its cache\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Event handlers for CodeInterpreter\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer with `AddEventHandler` registered\n220: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created\n221: - **THEN** the `OnAdd` callback SHALL be invoked with the new object\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Namespace-filtered informer\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` with namespace `production`\n226: - **WHEN** the factory starts\n227: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter informer SHALL only watch CodeInterpreters in `production` namespace\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Lister access from informer\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** a synced CodeInterpreter informer\n232: - **WHEN** `informer.Lister().Get(\"exec-1\")` is called\n233: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned from the local cache\n234: \n235: ### Requirement: Lister for CodeInterpreter\n236: \n237: The system SHALL generate `CodeInterpreterLister` and `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` under `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `List(selector)` and `Get(name)` methods.\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: List all CodeInterpreters\n240: \n241: - **GIVEN** a populated informer cache\n242: - **WHEN** `lister.List(labels.Everything())` is called\n243: - **THEN** all CodeInterpreters SHALL be returned from the cache\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Get by name and namespace\n246: \n247: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `exec-1` in namespace `default` exists in cache\n248: - **WHEN** `lister.CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Get(\"exec-1\")` is called\n249: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned or `NotFound` error if absent\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: List with label filter\n252: \n253: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters with various labels in cache\n254: - **WHEN** `lister.List(labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{\"type\": \"batch\"}))` is called\n255: - **THEN** only CodeInterpreters matching the label selector SHALL be returned\n256: \n257: ### Requirement: Fake clients for CodeInterpreter testing\n258: \n259: The system SHALL generate fake clients under `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` implementing `CodeInterpreterInterface` for unit testing.\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Unit test with fake client\n262: \n263: - **GIVEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset()` is called\n264: - **WHEN** `Create`, `Get`, `Update`, `Delete` are called on `fake.CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n265: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed in-memory without contacting K8s API\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Reactor for error injection\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** a fake client with `PrependReactor(\"create\", \"codeinterpreters\", ...)` that returns an error\n270: - **WHEN** `Create` is called on `CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n271: - **THEN** the reactor SHALL intercept and return the injected error\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Fake client pre-population\n274: \n275: - **GIVEN** a fake client created with `NewSimpleClientset(&existingCodeInterpreter)`\n276: - **WHEN** `Get(ctx, \"exec-1\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n277: - **THEN** the pre-populated CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned\n278: \n279: ### Requirement: Deepcopy generation for CodeInterpreter\n280: \n281: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterList` in `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` via `make gen-deepcopy`.\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: DeepCopy for CodeInterpreter\n284: \n285: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` object with populated spec and status\n286: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called\n287: - **THEN** a new `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be returned with all fields deeply copied\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: DeepCopy for CodeInterpreterSpec\n290: \n291: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSpec` with nested `ExecutionPolicy` and `ResourceQuota`\n292: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called\n293: - **THEN** all nested pointers SHALL be newly allocated\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: DeepCopyObject for runtime.Object interface\n296: \n297: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` used as `runtime.Object`\n298: - **WHEN** `DeepCopyObject()` is called\n299: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `runtime.Object` with a deep copy of the CodeInterpreter\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: Expansion interfaces for CodeInterpreter\n302: \n303: The system SHALL generate empty expansion interfaces `CodeInterpreterExpansion` in `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` and `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion` in `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go`.\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Client expansion interface\n306: \n307: - **GIVEN** the generated `CodeInterpreterExpansion` interface\n308: - **WHEN** a developer extends it with custom methods\n309: - **THEN** custom methods SHALL be available on `CodeInterpreterInterface` without regeneration\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Lister expansion interface\n312: \n313: - **GIVEN** the generated `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion` interface\n314: - **WHEN** a developer extends it with custom lister methods\n315: - **THEN** custom methods SHALL be available on `CodeInterpreterLister` without regeneration\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Scheme and codec registration for CodeInterpreter\n318: \n319: The system SHALL register CodeInterpreter types in `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` with `AddToScheme` functions for the generated client.\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Scheme registration at client init\n322: \n323: - **GIVEN** the `client-go` package is imported\n324: - **WHEN** `scheme.AddToScheme(runtimeScheme)` is called\n325: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types SHALL be recognizable by the scheme\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Negotiated serializer for CodeInterpreter\n328: \n329: - **GIVEN** a REST client with `NegotiatedSerializer`\n330: - **WHEN** encoding/decoding is needed for CodeInterpreter\n331: - **THEN** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` SHALL be supported with `application/json`\n332: \n333: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter resource plural\n334: \n335: The system SHALL use `codeinterpreters` as the REST resource plural for CodeInterpreter in client-go generated code.\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: Resource plural in typed client\n338: \n339: - **GIVEN** the generated `codeinterpreter.go` typed client\n340: - **WHEN** the REST client is configured\n341: - **THEN** `Resource(\"codeinterpreters\")` SHALL be used for API path construction\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Resource plural in lister\n344: \n345: - **GIVEN** the generated `codeinterpreter.go` lister\n346: - **WHEN** `NewCodeInterpreterLister` is called\n347: - **THEN** it SHALL use `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()` for the lister\n\n(End of file - total 347 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 ŌĆö CRD CodeInterpreter ń▒╗Õ×ŗÕ«Üõ╣ē Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the CodeInterpreter CRD type implementation including Go API types, validation, CRD manifests, client-go library, informers, and listers for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter API type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterSpec` types. `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL include `runtimeRef` (string), `code` (string), `language` (string), `executionPolicy` (ExecutionPolicy), and `resources` (ResourceQuota). `CodeInterpreter` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type registration\n\n- **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&CodeInterpreter{}, &CodeInterpreterList{})` is called during init\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be registered in the scheme with `Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`, `APIVersion = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime reference binding\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775847457670,"end":1775847457685}}}}
